1)  Ctrl + / = comment multiple selected lines
2)  There are two ways of closing all tabs in the editor, except the current one:
First, right-click the editor tab, and choose Close Others on the context menu.
Second, keeping the Alt key pressed, click   on the editor tab.
3) In PyCharm, you can have multiple cursors. Having pressed Alt, click the left mouse button at the desired position to set additional cursors in the editor.
Press Escape to remove all the additional cursors but one that resides at the line at caret.

